title: For Sale/Trade:  Sig Sauer P250C in .40 S&W with 2 Magazines
postcontent:
The title really says most of it.  I have, for sale or trade, a Sig P250C in .40 S&W.  It comes with the original case and I bought a second 13 round magazine for it.  The bottom of the mag is marked with glow-in-the-dark paint so it can be located if it's your nightstand gun.  

If you are not familiar with the model, the P250's fire control group is the serial numbered and traced part of the gun.  Any FCG can be assembled into a full size, compact or subcompact and is available in .380, 9mm, .357 Sig, .40 S&W and .45ACP.  You can assemble it with a compact slide on a subcompact grip module if you want barrel length without sacrificing concealability.  There are also spacers available if you want to purchase a full size mag and want to use it in a compact grip module.  The grip modules are cheap, so if you decide to "re-texture" and don't like how it came out, you can buy another grip module for, at the most, $50 from Sig and you're literally, good as new.  It is a Double Action Only with a smooth, light pull.  There is a short-pull trigger available.  This gun does not have one installed, but they're available for about $35.

These guns all came with a single magazine. For the compact .40/.357 Sig it is 13 rounds.  I like having a second magazine, so I bought another mag.  Anyone who knows Sig, knows they're proud of their magazines and Mec Gar doesn't make one for this model of gun.  An extra magazine is around $50.  

I'm not going to say this gun is Like New.  It's not.  It has also not been shot out.  The rifling in the barrel is still crisp and shiny.  The top of the barrel shows wear.  The top of the portion outside of the chamber is no longer black.  I have a number of additional detailed photos and can take more if there's anything you want to see.  It has plenty of life in it and it's a Sig. They design and build a top notch pistol, then they support it well.  

Most of all, I would prefer to trade and if the gun I'm getting is in prettier condition, I am willing to add cash, ammo or reloading powder to the deal.  When calculating the value of what I am trading, I want to make sure the second magazine is taken into consideration because they're not cheap.  I am willing to ship to an FFL at your expense, but it is ultimately your job to make sure it is legal for you to own.  If you live in a state that limits magazine capacity, we can negotiate on that point.  If you get denied on your NICS check, we'll need to discuss a resolution.

title: For Sale:  Become an NRA Rifle Instructor this weekend only
postcontent:
Do what you love, and train others to love it too. The NRA basic rifle course is a very popular course, and it is the nation wide standard for all of those looking to be trained. You will learn how to use the tried and true NRA method of training. Your students will feel a sense of accomplishment knowing that they were trained the right way when they have an NRA certified instructor standing behind them as their mentor.

Your students will walk away with a nationally recognized certificate and the NRA rifle shooting handbook. This course is held at Delaware valley sports center in northeast Philadelphia. When you become an NRA instructor you will have access to special discounts on training gear through the NRA store. You will also have access to the NRA training materials center.

Upon completion of this course you will be able to certify your students in two ways 1. with the 3 hour “First steps rifle orientation” and 2. with the 14 hour “Basic rifle course”.

I do require instructor candidates to be NRA members with a current ID number. Copy/paste this web address https://membership.nrahq.org/forms/signup.asp?campaignid=XI029126 to get the lowest price possible and help uphold our rights. The NRA has a credentialing fee of $30 for a 2-yr term you will do this after the class on the NRA website.

This is a two part course lasting a total of 20 hrs over two days, 10 hrs per day.  

Part one: 6hrs  “Basic Instructor Training” (BIT). The BIT is required for all new NRA instructors and costs $75. The BIT is the first portion of the course and it will be held on Saturday Oct. 25 2014 from 9am – 3pm.  

Part two: 14hrs Rifle Instructor portion cost $175. This is required by everyone attending. Those of you who are already NRA instructors can arrive at 3pm on Saturday Oct. 25 2014 and at this time we will begin the Rifle Instructor course. 3pm – 7pm and Sunday Oct. 26 2014 9am – 7pm

Bring eye and ear protection 20 rounds of factory ammunition (no reloads) and 1 rifle anywhere from 22lr to .308 Win. No 30-06 or higher if you don’t have a rifle that fits these parameters i will loan you an AR-15 just supply the ammunition.

title: For Sale:  Concealed Weapons Permit Class (aka Concealed Carry Course) for $59
postcontent:
One of the requirements by the State of Florida to apply for a concealed weapons permit is to have successfully taken a concealed carry course under a certified instructor. Miami Shooters Club provides such a course with its team of NRA certified instructors - who will teach students the important fundamentals of how to safely use a semi-automatic pistol and revolver. Your concealed weapons permit will allow you to concealed carry in more than 30 states.

Miami Shooters Club's instructors carry multiple certifications under the NRA, have traveled abroad to train and receive firearm certifications, and are hand-to-hand self defense experts - having taught multiple seminars for the Miami Dade Police Department. Under their instruction in the concealed carry class, students will learn the mechanisms behind pistols and how they operate while learning how to grip the firearm, aim, pull the trigger, get into a proper stance, and much more. The class also covers many of the legal issues and expected ethics of concealed carry in Florida. The classes are designed for complete beginners who have never touched a gun before... but experienced shooters will learn something as well.

At the end of the classroom portion, students will safely discharge a pistol under the supervision of a certified instructor, as required by the State of Florida. Miami Shooters Club will provide a firearm, ammunition, eye protection, and ear protection at no extra cost.

Classes take place in Miami on Fridays at 6:30pm or on Saturdays at 1pm.
